CHANGES IN Mar.utils VERSION 2.0.0

  BREAKING CHANGES:

  o Most database functions no longer accept Oracle credentials directly
  o New requirement to establish Oracle connection before calling functions
  o Functions that save Protected B data now use encryption by default
  o Some legacy parameter names and unused options removed
  o See README.md for migration examples using ROracle::dbConnect()

  NEW FEATURES:

  o Added save_encrypted() and load_encrypted() functions for Protected B data
  o Enhanced security for sensitive data storage following DFO protocols

CHANGES IN Mar.utils VERSION 2019.12.19

  IMPROVEMENTS:

  o Changed 'quiet' parameter to 'quietly' for consistency with other Mar.* functions

CHANGES IN Mar.utils VERSION 2019.12.10

  NEW FEATURES:

  o Adds option to prevent status message output from make_oracle_cxn()

CHANGES IN Mar.utils VERSION 2019.07.29

  IMPROVEMENTS:

  o Removes @importFrom from all documentation so external functions aren't exported

CHANGES IN Mar.utils VERSION 2019.07.04

